body:
Thank you for making this great project

I have packaged the problematic design into a [dedicated repo](https://github.com/FurryAcetylCoA/verilator-bug1).
In short, the minimized design looks like
``` verilog
module CPU(input wire clock, cpu_reset);
  reg         reset_r;	
  always @(posedge clock) begin	
    reset_r <= cpu_reset;	 // The problematic one
  end 
endmodule

module TOP(input clock, reset);
  reg sync_0, sync_1, sync_2;	
  wire _cpu_reset_chain_io_q = sync_0;	
  CPU cpu ( .clock(clock),
            .cpu_reset(_cpu_reset_chain_io_q | reset) 
  );
  always @(posedge clock) begin
    sync_0 <= sync_1;	
    sync_1 <= sync_2;
    sync_2 <= reset;	
  end
endmodule
```
I tested in `Verilator 5.023 devel rev v5.020-121-ga69cb9b0` and `Verilator 5.022`

This same design also generate an Infinite recursion with flag `-O0`. As described in the repo mentioned.


Please let me know if you need any more info.

Thanks!
